-- Wen Leaves Pakistan After Committing $25 Billion
-- B y   F a r h a n   S h a r i f
-- 2010-12-19T08:52:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/wen-ends-three-day-pakistan-visit-after-committing-to-25-bln-investment.html
Chinese Premier  Wen Jiabao  left
Pakistan after completing a three-day official visit and
committing to investment worth $25 billion.  Wen and his delegation were seen in a televised ceremony at
Chaklala Air Base in Rawalpindi, where Pakistan’s Prime Minister
 Syed Yousuf Raza Gilani , members of the federal Cabinet and
other officials were present.  China and Pakistan signed agreements and memorandums of
understandings to bring about $25 billion in Chinese investment
to Pakistan within the next three years, according to the state-
run Associated Press of Pakistan. Wen addressed a joint session
of Parliament before leaving for China.  The two governments also agreed to conduct currency swaps,
according to a joint  statement  published by China’s official
Xinhua News Agency.  Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
Ltd. , China’s biggest lender, decided to open subsidiaries in
Islamabad and Karachi, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Farhan Sharif  in Karachi at 
